# MARS – environment variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the keys you need.
# The CLI auto-loads .env on startup (python-dotenv, no extra setup).

# ── GitHub Copilot (free with a Copilot subscription) ───────────────────────
#
# 1. Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 2. Generate a classic token (no extra scopes needed)
# 3. Paste it here:
#
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# GH_TOKEN and GITHUB_COPILOT_TOKEN are also accepted.

# ── Anthropic Claude (paid) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# ANTHROPIC_KEY is also accepted.

# ── Ollama (free, local) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# No key needed. Install from https://ollama.com, then:
#   ollama serve
#   ollama pull llama3.2
#
# Start MARS with:
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider ollama --model llama3.2

# ── Mock (offline testing, no key) ──────────────────────────────────────────
#
# python -m mars.cli.main --provider mock

# ── Usage examples ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider copilot
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider anthropic
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider anthropic --model claude-opus-4-7
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider ollama --model llama3.2
#   python -m mars.cli.main --provider mock
#
# Or spawn agents inside the CLI:
#   /spawn copilot
#   /spawn anthropic claude-opus-4-7
#   /spawn ollama llama3.2
#   /spawn mock
